| Aphidius colemani     | Tiny wasp        | Slender, 2-3mm long. Looks similar to small, winged, black ants, but with long antennae. | Many aphid species, particularly green peach aphid, cotton/melon aphid and wheat aphid. | Biological Services |
| Aphidius ervi         | Tiny wasp        | Slender, 4-5mm long. Similar to small, winged, black ants, but with long antennae. | Many species, particularly foxglove aphid, potato aphid and pea aphids                                                                                                                                           | Biological Services |
| Orius tantillus       | Pirate bug       | Nymphs are light brown to orange in colour wingless and have red eyes. They range in size from about 2-4mm.